        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 1:03PM EDT by NWS Binghamton NY</headline>
        <description>At 103 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Pecks Pond, or 13 miles west of Montague, moving northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Bushkill, Barryville, Oakland, Glen Spey, Rowland, Smallwood, Tusten,
White Lake, Dingmans Ferry, and Lackawaxen.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
